        "timestamp": "2020-03-23 11:52:45.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI thought that this patchset was applied in https://gerrit.onap.org/r/c/sdc/+/102596 commit in the patchset 3 but unfortunately that patchset was empty.\nFor that reason currently, the sdc-BE-init will be failing when will try to updateNormative (re-run the docker_run.sh). The reason is that onap/base_sdc-python doesn't have the yaml python package. So we can instead of catching the 'yaml.YAMLError' we can simply catch the general Exception, or update the base_sdc-python to had the yaml package:\nhttps://gerrit.onap.org/r/gitweb?p=sdc/sdc-docker-base.git;a=blob;f=base_sdc-python/Dockerfile;h=96e4eb8a8e214536d3181f896fc8f26aabb1c8d4;hb=refs/heads/master#l22\n\nI apologize for my mistake.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
